Apart from the distinctive materials—Table 2—and the specific spoke designs—Figure 5 and Figure 6—in addition to Equations (1) and (2), the parameters under examination also encompassed the following:
The number of spokes: varied between 15 and 25;
The thickness of the outer ring: ranged from 1.5mm to 6mm for GFRPs and 1mm to 4mm for CFRPs;
The fiber orientation: set at 0, 15, or 30 degrees relative to the longitudinal direction;
The thickness of the spokes: tailored for each concept to achieve the prescribed vertical tire stiffness.
